text: Fatma El Sharnouby (born November 18, 1997) is an Egyptian middle-distance runner. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 800 metres race; her time of 2:21.24 in the heats did not qualify her for the semifinals. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Egyptian female middle-distance runners Category:Olympic athletes of Egypt Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics
